'''Fvwm''' (F? Virtual Window Manager for X11) is a window manager for X11.  It is designed to minimize memory consumption, provide a 3D look to window frames, and a virtual desktop. Fvwm is now in the portage tree and you can install it by using:

{{Emerge|x11-wm/fvwm}}

== Use flags ==

<code>gtk2-perl</code> = Enable GTK2 Perl bindings<br />
<code>lock</code> = Enable screen locking<br />
<code>netpbm</code> = Enable NetPBM support (used by FvwmScript-ScreenDump)<br />
<code>rplay</code> = Enable rplay support<br />
<code>stroke</code> = Mouse Gesture support<br />
<code>perl</code> = FvwmPerl support<br />

== Configuration ==

=== Configuration for launching fvwm ===

{{File|~/.xinitrc||<pre>
<nowiki>exec /usr/bin/ck-launch-session /usr/bin/dbus-launch /usr/bin/fvwm
</nowiki></pre>
}}

